{"title_page": "Ashley, Test Valley", "text_new": "{{Dablink|This article is about the village in the Test Valley district. For other uses, see [[Ashley, East Hampshire]] or [[Ashley, New Forest]].}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox UK place\n|country = England\n|static_image_name=St Mary, Ashley.jpg\n|coordinates = {{coord|51.077|-1.452|display=inline,title}}\n|official_name      =Ashley\n|population = 72\n|shire_district= [[Test Valley]]\n|shire_county= [[Hampshire]]\n|metropolitan_borough=   \n| metropolitan_county = \n|region=South East England\n|constituency_westminster= [[Romsey and Southampton North (UK Parliament constituency)|Romsey and Southampton North]]\n|post_town= STOCKBRIDGE\n|postcode_district = SO20\n|postcode_area= SO\n|dial_code= 01794\n|os_grid_reference= SU385310\n}}\n'''Ashley''' is a village and [[civil parish]] in the [[Test Valley]] district of [[Hampshire]], England, {{convert|8|mi}} west of [[Winchester]]. Its nearest town is [[Stockbridge, Hampshire|Stockbridge]], which lies 2.6 miles (4.2&nbsp;km) north-west. At the [[United Kingdom Census 2001|2001 census]] the parish had a population of 72.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://neighbourhood.statistics.gov.uk/dissemination/viewFullDataset.do?instanceSelection=03070&productId=779&$ph=60_61&datasetInstanceId=3070&startColumn=1&numberOfColumns=8&containerAreaId=790412 | title=Neighbourhood Statistics: Full Dataset View: Test Valley (Non-Metropolitan District) | work=Neighbourhood Statistics | publisher=[[Office for National Statistics]] | accessdate=2008-10-12 }}</ref> It is in the [[civil parish]] of [[King's Somborne]].  [[Ashley Castle]] is in the village.\n\n==See also==\n*[[St Mary's Church, Ashley]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:Test Valley]]\n\n\n{{Hampshire-geo-stub}}\n\n[[nl:Ashley (Hampshire)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Dablink|This article is about the village in the Test Valley district. For other uses, see [[Ashley, East Hampshire]] or [[Ashley, New Forest]].}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox UK place\n|country = England\n|static_image_name=St Mary, Ashley.jpg\n|coordinates = {{coord|51.077|-1.452|display=inline,title}}\n|official_name      =Ashley\n|population = 72\n|shire_district= [[Test Valley]]\n|shire_county= [[Hampshire]]\n|metropolitan_borough=   \n| metropolitan_county = \n|region=South East England\n|constituency_westminster= [[Romsey and Southampton North (UK Parliament constituency)|Romsey and Southampton North]]\n|post_town= STOCKBRIDGE\n|postcode_district = SO20 6\n|postcode_area= SO\n|dial_code= 01794\n|os_grid_reference= SU385310\n}}\n'''Ashley''' is a village and [[civil parish]] in the [[Test Valley]] district of [[Hampshire]], England, {{convert|8|mi}} west of [[Winchester]]. Its nearest town is [[Stockbridge, Hampshire|Stockbridge]], which lies 2.6 miles (4.2&nbsp;km) north-west. At the [[United Kingdom Census 2001|2001 census]] the parish had a population of 72.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://neighbourhood.statistics.gov.uk/dissemination/viewFullDataset.do?instanceSelection=03070&productId=779&$ph=60_61&datasetInstanceId=3070&startColumn=1&numberOfColumns=8&containerAreaId=790412 | title=Neighbourhood Statistics: Full Dataset View: Test Valley (Non-Metropolitan District) | work=Neighbourhood Statistics | publisher=[[Office for National Statistics]] | accessdate=2008-10-12 }}</ref> It is in the [[civil parish]] of [[King's Somborne]].  [[Ashley Castle]] is in the village.\n\n==See also==\n*[[St Mary's Church, Ashley]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:Test Valley]]\n\n\n{{Hampshire-geo-stub}}\n\n[[nl:Ashley (Hampshire)]]\n", "name_user": "AJP", "label": "safe", "comment": "postcode district only", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashley,_Test_Valley"}
